`hide.bs.collapse` is a custom event and you are not listing to the `events` of the sidebar here. You are listening to all of them.

So inside, you want to filter to events from the `sidebar`.
Something like:
```js
sidebar.addEventListener('hide.bs.collapse', function (e) {
  if (e.target && e.target.id === 'sidebar-wrapper') {
    document.getElementById('main-container').classList.add('toggled');
    console.log(e)
  }
})
```

Also, nitpick but use [arrow functions](https://www.w3schools.com/js/js_arrow_function.asp). Browsers support these in today's world.

